<title type="html"><![CDATA[Games which display attribute tables?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4798&amp;p=42502#p42502"><![CDATA[
Slalom uses it to display a row of black pixels above the top status bar.<br />Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles and Mario 3 just have graphical glitches being displayed.  You can see "51" partially displayed on TMNT's title screen in the very top row, and some graphics garbage at the top of the screen in the sidescrolling areas.  Super Mario 3 displays some junk during the title screen after Luigi whacks the top of the screen and causes the screen to shake, it's using negative scroll values causing attribute tables to be drawn at the top.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Thu Jan 29, 2009 4:46 pm</p><hr />
